value: Breeds from the Afghanistan frontier throughout the Himalayas to Assam, western and central China, Manchuria, and Japan from Hondo to Kiusiu. Winters in southern India, Ceylon and the Andaman Islands; recorded from eastern China, the Bonin Islands, Formosa, Riu Kiu Islands, Cochinchina, etc., as a migrant or straggler.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Palearctic winter visitor (from Asia), thick savanna woodland: SE Kenya - SE DRC - most of Mozambique.
South and east Asia; winters pen. India, Sri Lanka and e Africa
